        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 2:01AM CDT by NWS Hastings NE</headline>
        <description>At 200 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Hebron to near Oak.
Movement was southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Hebron, Deshler, and Ruskin around 205 AM CDT.
Gilead around 220 AM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
